### 3. JavaScript Architecture

#### APRONIXChat Class (app.js)

**Properties:**
```javascript
chatHistory          // Array of messages in current chat
currentChatId        // ID of active chat
allChats            // Object of all saved chats
apiKey              // Gemini API key from localStorage
currentTheme        // Current active theme
```

**Methods:**

**Initialization:**
- `constructor()` - Initialize the chat application
- `initializeElements()` - Cache DOM elements
- `attachEventListeners()` - Attach event handlers
- `loadSettings()` - Load API key and theme
- `applyTheme()` - Apply theme to document

**Chat Management:**
- `startNewChat()` - Create new chat
- `loadChatHistory()` - Load chats from storage
- `loadChat(chatId)` - Load specific chat
- `saveChatHistory()` - Save to localStorage
- `deleteChat(chatId)` - Delete chat
- `renderHistoryList()` - Render sidebar history

**Message Handling:**
- `sendMessage(e)` - Send user message
- `callGeminiAPI(userMessage)` - Call Gemini API
- `addLoadingMessage(id)` - Add loading animation
- `removeLoadingMessage(id)` - Remove loading state
- `showErrorMessage(text)` - Show error bubble
- `updateDisplay()` - Update UI based on state
- `renderMessages()` - Render all messages
- `autoResizeInput()` - Auto-expand textarea

**Settings Management:**
- `openSettings()` - Show settings modal
- `closeSettings()` - Hide settings modal
- `saveSettings()` - Save API key and theme
- `toggleAPIKeyVisibility()` - Show/hide API key
- `selectTheme(element)` - Select theme
- `showNotification(message)` - Show notification

